Data Consolidation: Collects data from multiple sources into one place, making it easier to process uniformly.

Enhanced Data Quality: Cleanses data through deduplication, error correction and standardization before loading.

Schema Alignment: Maps and converts different source formats into a unified schema for the warehouse.

Improved Performance: Handles heavy transformations outside the warehouse to ensure faster analytical queries.

Temporary Storage for Batches: Stores incoming data temporarily so it can be synchronized and 
                               loaded in organized batches.

Better Data Security: Provides a controlled zone where sensitive data undergoes ETL with proper security measures.

Audit & Traceability: Maintains logs of all ETL steps, enabling full data lineage and easier troubleshooting.
